package.json
> First file in that run in the application
> Entry point to app
> MetaData (name,description,version)
> All the dependencies
> Scripts (start,build,test)

//////Step to generate package.json
* NodeJs must be installed in laptop
> go inside the folder where you want package.json
> npm init 
> Answer all question

//////Step to install packages
* NodeJs must be installed in laptop
> go inside the folder where you want to install
> npm i packagename/npm install packagename
npm i packagename@version 

package-lock > dependency tree
.gitignore > all those thing i want to avoid pushing
node_modules > all packages of app

>>>>When we get new app
* npm i

Step To Create React App
# window
* One time step
> open cmd as administrator
> npm i -g create-react-app

# Every time you need new app
> open cmd/terminal
> go inside folder
> create-react-app appname

# mac/linux
* One time step
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

# Every time you need new app
> open terminal
> go inside folder
> create-react-app appname

------------------------------------------
################################
> Open cmd
> npx create-react-app appname

///////Step to run react app
> open terminal/cmd
> go inside folder
> npm start


///////
react > Main package of the application
react-dom > help to load content on the browser
react-scripts > help to run the application


function add(a,b){
    return a,b
}
add(2,5)
5
add(5,2)
2

function add(a,b){
    var out = [a,b]
    return out
}

add(2,5)
2

add(2,5)
[2, 5]

HTML > Raws Structure
CSS > Design part of application
JS > Logical Part


head> links,css,js,title
body> what ever is visible to the user


block element
> Always start from new line
> occupies the whole width of the screen
> Div p 

inline element
> Start in the same line 
> only take space according to content
> span a


